article.description: — Zach Scott scored 24 points, including the game-winning 3-pointer as time expired, and McNeese State defeated 78-75 on Saturday.
article.headline: Scott hits winner, McNeese edges Houston Baptist 78-75
article.linkText: Scott hits winner, McNeese edges Houston Baptist 78-75
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. -- — Zach Scott scored 24 points, including the game-winning 3-pointer as time expired, and McNeese State defeated 78-75 on Saturday. Scott took a pass a little right of the top of the key, pumped fake and stepped left before letting the winner fly. It was his fifth 3-pointer on seven attempts. Collin Warren added 21 points for the Cowboys (7-11, 1-0 Southland Conference). Myles Lewis scored 13 points with seven rebounds. Kellon Taylor had 12 points with five assists. Darius Lee had 18 points and eight rebounds for the Huskies (4-10, 0-1). Brycen Long scored 15 points. Jade Tse added 11.
